                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "interaction",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> The tardigrade would be reduced to 0 Hit Points or die due to starvation, suffocation, or similar environmental causes</p>\n<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per week</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong> The tardigrade isn't already in Tun State</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> The tardigrade doesn't die but instead remains at 1 Hit Point and curls into a dry ball, called a tun. While in this state, the tardigrade is @UUID[Compendium.sf2e.conditions.Item.Unconscious]; doesn't need to eat, drink, or breathe; and increases its resistance to 20. It remains in Tun State indefinitely until covered in significant amounts of water, at which point it begins to rehydrate, gaining regeneration 5. The regeneration persists until the star tardigrade reaches maximum Hit Points. The tardigrade then exits its Tun State.</p>"
                },
                "frequency": {
                    "max": 1,
                    "per": "P1W"
                },
